7 PROPOSED COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
8 An Act relating to Oklahoma Agricultural Extension;
prohibiting the required centralization and
9 redirection of local revenues; authorizing local
funds be held by local financial institutions;
10 prohibiting comingling with state or federal funds;
providing for codification; and declaring an
11 emergency.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3419.1 of Title 70, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. No entity or division under the control of the Board of
19 Regents for the Oklahoma Agricultural and Mechanical Colleges,
20 including but not limited to, the Oklahoma Agricultural Extension
21 Division, shall directly, or as a condition of receiving Oklahoma
22 Agricultural Extension Division services or access to Oklahoma
23 Agricultural Experiment Station programming, require funding
24 generated at the local level be:
Req. No. 16151 Page 1

1 1. Centralized at the division or station; or
2 2. Directed or expended outside the county in which the funding
3 was generated.
4 B. Local level funds may be held in accounts at local financial
5 institutions, provided such accounts shall not comingle local funds
6 with state or federal funds.
7 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
8 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
9 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
10 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
